title: 'Scared' British family told they cannot leave their Greece hotel after 'biblical' rainfall
description: A "scared" British family have been told they cannot leave their hotel on Skiathos after the Greek resort island was hit by torrential rain and flooding.

title: Body of child pulled from sea off southern Ireland
description: The body of a young girl has been recovered from the sea off the coast of southern Ireland.

title: 'Trafficked' Cubans being coerced to fight for Russia in Ukraine, govt says
description: A human trafficking ring that coerced Cubans to fight for Russia in Ukraine has been uncovered, the Caribbean island's government says.

title: British-made Challenger 2 tank destroyed by Russian troops, officials say
description: Russian forces have destroyed a British-made tank on the battlefield in Ukraine, Kremlin officials have said.

title: Spanish women's football team coach sacked in wake of Rubiales kiss
description: The Spanish women's football team manager, Jorge Vilda, has been sacked in the wake of the Rubiales kiss furore, Reuters reports.

title: Spanish FA apologises for 'enormous' damage caused by Rubiales kiss as it promises improvements
description: The Royal Spanish Football Federation (RFEF) has apologised for the "enormous damage done" in the wake of Luis Rubiales' kiss, saying his actions do not reflect the federation and they're "embarrassed" by his actions.

title: The Chinese economy is faltering – should the rest of the world worry?
description: China's economy has slipped into deflation as consumer prices declined in July for the first time in more than two years.

title: Greenwood welcomed by fans as he trains for first time at new club
description: Mason Greenwood has been welcomed by fans of his new team in Spain after leaving Manchester United on loan.

title: TikTok opens new European centre in bid to combat privacy concerns
description: TikTok's first European data centre has gone live as the Chinese-owned company seeks to combat long-held privacy concerns.

title: Plane crashes during gender reveal party stunt, killing pilot
description: A plane has crashed as it performed a stunt at a gender reveal party in Mexico, killing the pilot.

title: Why isn't Russia running out of ammunition in Ukraine?
description: Is Russia running out of ammunition? It's a question Ukraine and its allies have been pondering as the war continues well into its second year.

title: At least one dead as cars washed away during Greece storm with 7,000 lightning bolts recorded
description: At least one person has died as a torrential storm batters parts of Greece, leaving many homes and roads flooded.

title: Cancer cases grow by 79% in young people - as 'alarming' study suggests key reasons
description: Cancer cases among young people across the world have grown by 79%, according to an "alarming" study.

title: Two workers detained after digging hole for shortcut through Great Wall of China
description: Two construction workers have been detained by police in China for damaging a section of the Great Wall.

title: Tennis star stops US Open match after fan 'sings Hitler anthem'
description: A tennis fan was kicked out of a US Open match after allegedly "singing the anthem of Hitler" during a match involving German player Alexander Zverev.

title: Sara Sharif's family being 'harassed' by police, says grandfather
description: The grandfather of Sara Sharif has urged his son to "present himself" to police and give his "point of view" following the 10-year-old girl's death.

title: 'General Armageddon pictured alive' after weeks of speculation following Wagner mutiny
description: Russian general Sergei Surovikin - not seen since the Wagner Group mutiny - has apparently reappeared.
